{
  "id": 15514,
  "name": "Generate multi-agent research reports with Tavily, Groq, Notion and Supabase",
  "totalViews": 0,
  "price": 0,
  "purchaseUrl": null,
  "user": {
    "id": 104702,
    "name": "Redowan Ahmed Farhan",
    "username": "redowanfarhan",
    "bio": "Automation focused builder creating practical, scalable workflows with n8n. I design real world automations that reduce manual work, improve efficiency, and connect tools seamlessly. Here to contribute by sharing reusable workflows, exploring use cases, and learning from the community while building reliable, impactful systems.\n",
    "verified": true,
    "links": "[\"\"]",
    "avatar": "https://gravatar.com/avatar/6f87cd2199c26ec1a0b3b72c8352a0ddeaeafafef24d3301963cc2c126d5e084?r=pg&d=retro&size=200"
  },
  "description": "How it works\nA manual trigger sets the research topic and generates three parallel Tavily web search queries\nA Summarizer Agent (Groq Llama 3.3 70B) and an Analyst Agent (OpenRouter GPT) process the search results simultaneously, producing a factual summary and a deep trend analysis\nA Synthesis Agent (Groq Llama 3.3 70B) combines both outputs into a structured executive report with key findings, strategic implications, and recommended actions\nThe report is chunked and saved as a new Notion database page, then embedded with OpenAI and indexed in Supabase for semantic search\n\nSet up steps\nAdd your Tavily, Groq, and OpenRouter API credentials (~10 min)\nConnect Notion OAuth2 and point the node to your target database\nAdd your Supabase credentials and confirm your documents table has a vector column",
  "createdAt": "2026-05-06T17:53:39.511Z",
